Red Lake County is a county located in the U.S. state of Minnesota. As of the 2010 census, the population was 4,089. Its county seat is Red Lake Falls.
It is one of only twelve counties in the state of Minnesota that doesn't have a stop light within the county, and is also known as the only county in the U.S. that is surrounded by just two neighboring counties.
